Pending → Building → Completed → Shipped
with the safety rails:
	•	Cancel Order
	•	Cancel Build (inventory returned)
	•	Reopen Order
	•	StockMovement ledger
	•	Order notes + audit trail

Where the system now stands (architecturally)

You now have a pretty clean separation:

Orders
	•	business workflow
	•	customer + shipping

Builds
	•	production activity
	•	consumes components

StockMovement
	•	immutable inventory ledger
	•	source of truth for stock changes

Order Notes
	•	lightweight audit trail
	•	human context

This is exactly the structure used in many real ERP/MRP systems, just simplified.
